## 1. Files and their purpose

| File | Purpose | Loading | Updated |
|---|---|---|---|
| `ActualStatus.md` | Current state: where we are, what's done, what's next | **Auto (each session)** | End of sprint + end of each significant session |
| `Sprint.md` | Planned work: sprints, sub-sprints, micros, work-orders | **Auto (each session)** | On any plan change or task completion |
| `Sprint_Done.md` | Archive of finished sprints | On demand | When a macro closes (move it here) |
| `COMMITTENTE.md` | The human cockpit | On demand | When the way of working changes |
| `<dept>/STATUS.md` | A department's domain register (facts) | On demand | By that department |
| `<dept>/INTERFACE.md` | Async mailbox manager ↔ department | On demand | At session boundaries (see §2.3) |

**Auto-loaded once at session start:** `ActualStatus.md` + `Sprint.md`. Don't re-read them mid-session — the context already has them.

**⚠️ The disk wins.** Execution and department sessions **re-read `ActualStatus.md` + the current `Sprint.md` section from disk at the start of every hand-off, before acting** — the manager may have rewritten them after this session loaded. On any discrepancy between memory and disk, **disk wins.**

